UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SJR 139/EN
1 A JOINT RESOLUTION designating honorary names for various roads and
2 bridges.
3 WHEREAS, from time to time, the General Assembly has seen fit to honor various
4 Kentuckians by naming portions of state highways and erecting commemorative roadway
5 signs in their honor; and
6 WHEREAS, these Kentuckians have come from all walks of life, held a multitude
7 of jobs, and had a variety of accomplishments that made them deserving of the honor;
8 and
9 WHEREAS, these individuals have included former Governors, former members of
10 the General Assembly, decorated veterans, slain law enforcement officers, local elected
11 officials, astronauts, doctors, educators, distinguished athletes, and civic leaders; and
12 WHEREAS, every citizen of the Commonwealth owes a great debt of gratitude to
13 the patriotic men and women killed and wounded in service to their country in times of
14 great need; and
15 WHEREAS, the General Assembly has often honored the veterans of this state by
16 naming portions of several roads, from interstates to small two-lane country roads, in
17 their honor; and
18 WHEREAS, the General Assembly again sees fit to honor a group of individuals
19 who have made the lives of their fellow Kentuckians better and brought honor and
20 respect to the Commonwealth;
21 NOW, THEREFORE,
22 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
23 Section 1. The Transportation Cabinet shall designate United States Route 60A
24 in Jefferson County, from the intersection with Kentucky Route 61 (mile point 4.547) to
25 the intersection with Kentucky Route 864 (mile point 5.520), as the "Officer Peter
26 Grignon Memorial Highway" and shall, within 30 days of the effective date of this
27 Resolution, erect appropriate signs denoting this designation.
